ook analyzes forms of authority that emerge as an official institution seeks to incorporate and manage diverse perspectives on recent violence.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCollective memoryzPeru. 0aHistorical museumszPeru. 0aNational museumszPeru. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aPeru, Place of Memory, LUM, Peruvian government, museum, postwar Peru, memorial museums, globalized museums, human rights, NGOs, Peruvian army, tolerance, social inclusion, Tolerance, and Social Inclusion, Lima, postwar, Communist Party of Peru, Shining Path, civil war in Peru, 1980s, Fernando Belaunde.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073913840uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197880957440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978809574423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978809574/original  a978-3-11-073913-8  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK